@startuml
title POST /api/v1/codes — Permission Denied (403)
autonumber

actor Client
participant "codes_collection()\n_create_codes()" as View
participant "create_registration\n_codes()" as Service
participant "_can_generate\n_code_type()" as PermCheck

== Teacher tries to create TEACHER code ==
Client -> View: POST /codes\n{codeType: "TEACHER", ...}\n[JWT: teacher user]
View -> Service: create_registration_codes(\ncreator=teacher, type=TEACHER)
Service -> PermCheck: _can_generate_code_type(\nteacher, TEACHER)
PermCheck -> PermCheck: primary_role = TEACHER\nTEACHER can only create STUDENT
PermCheck --> Service: False
Service --x View: PermissionError
View --x Client: 403 "Not authorized to\ngenerate this code type"

== Researcher without sudo tries STUDENT code ==
Client -> View: POST /codes\n{codeType: "STUDENT", ...}\n[JWT: researcher, no CREATE_STUDENT sudo]
View -> Service: create_registration_codes(\ncreator=researcher, type=STUDENT)
Service -> PermCheck: _can_generate_code_type(\nresearcher, STUDENT)
PermCheck -> PermCheck: primary_role = RESEARCHER\nSTUDENT requires CREATE_STUDENT sudo
PermCheck -> PermCheck: has_sudo_permission(CREATE_STUDENT)? No
PermCheck --> Service: False
Service --x View: PermissionError
View --x Client: 403 "Not authorized to\ngenerate this code type"

note over PermCheck
  **Permission Matrix:**
  Admin: RESEARCHER only
  Researcher: TEACHER always,
    STUDENT with CREATE_STUDENT sudo,
    RESEARCHER with CREATE_RESEARCHER_CODES sudo
  Teacher: STUDENT only
end note
@enduml
